In Android phone security settings, allow installation of apps from unknown sources.
Install each application package directly on phones running Android 4.2 (Jelly Bean) or above.

Instructional App = course material + Android app

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Verify Downloads

Prerequisites: gnupg (https://www.gnupg.org/)

To verify the authenticity of the application packages in a terminal:
$ gpg --keyserver hkps://keys.openpgp.org:443 --recv-keys 0x4191f431
$ gpg --verify SHA1SUMS.gpg SHA1SUMS

To verify the integrity of the application packages in a terminal:
Ubuntu: $ sha1sum -c SHA1SUMS
macOS: $ shasum -a 1 -c SHA1SUMS

Windows: 
$ ls *.apk | Get-FileHash -Algorithm SHA1
$ Get-Content .\SHA1SUMS
(check that hashes match)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[Notes]

informal_field_test.apk and focus_groups.apk are identical

If one verifies authenticity and integrity using Windows Subsystem for Linux, the terminal may output "BAD signature" and "FAILED open or read."
If so, convert checksum files to Unix format, and retry.
$ sudo apt install dos2unix
$ dos2unix SHA1SUMS
$ gpg --verify SHA1SUMS.gpg SHA1SUMS
$ sha1sum -c SHA1SUMS